oms “Conway’s work is an important addition to, and corrective to, the existing literature on Canadian populism, socialism, and to the history of Saskatchewan and the CCF. It is also an intellectually interesting consideration of the role of political leadership in a social movement.” James Naylor, author of The Fate of Labour Socialism “Conway has recovered and placed in context the life of George H. Williams, whose significance in the organization of Canadian farmers and the development of the CCF in Saskatchewan is richly demonstrated here.” Kirk Niergarth, author of The Dignity of Every Human Being  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgriculture and politicszSaskatchewanxHistoryy20th century. 0aFarmersxPolitical activityzSaskatchewanxHistoryy20th century. 0aPoliticianszSaskatchewanvBiography. 0aPopulismzSaskatchewanxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialismzSaskatchewanxHistoryy20th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aWilliams, George Hara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977546640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889775466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889775466/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles